content_vision: We are lost. Why my girlfriend and her friends go against me. Why our relationship cannot survive? What the hell do we want? Never tell a lie. Miss me when a new day comes now.
structure_suggestion_description: Slow club banger. Heartbroken with seductive intro
text:
Intro:
i'll grind day and night, i'll make it right, no need for a pause,
oh yeah!!! my hustle, he ain't trippin', he knows it's mandatory for my cause.

Verse 1:
beat after beat, i gotta grind for that guap,
'til you were sick of him, almost must've been mocked,
but i'll show you, they are futile, my work won't stop.
we've been waiting, just waiting for the hammer to fall
but we'll keep living like we're eternal and giving a taste of our love to all.
i'll give you just a little taste, of my undying love that won't go to waste,
we're inseparable, like two stars in space.
so maybe we could get down now,

Chorus 1:
the haters keep talking, don't phase me
we'll stay real, don't let them sway me
and you did all that you can, can't blame me.
it's not just about the looks we make, all artificial,

Verse 2:
you may not approve, but we're just having fun
we'll keep living it up, spinning it 'til we're done.
come get to know us, from beyond this realm,
our vibes so strong, it's like we're at the helm.
just had to get that good vibe back,
took 50 out the bank,
feeling so spiritual, like love is my only bank.
nature knows true love when it sees it,

Chorus 2:
my temperature rising, rockets burning like combs,
you take it then leave me, my love gets me high and then roams.
my cup muddy, but i ain't never sweatin',
the congregation gathered, the energy's settin'.

Verse 3:
he said, 'why you gotta be so kind? ',
and i asked, 'say to me what you want from me? '
but his silence hung heavy, like it wasn't meant to be.
do the gangsta run, in this crazy ass place,
all y'all niggas man, just tryin' to keep pace.
this girl got me feeling hella scarce,
that's why i gotta kill all these underwear monsters in her drawers.
rise a succubus, got a young nigga with a hundred grand,

Chorus 3:
my brains dusted, she threw me all in,
now i can't even think, she's my downfall, i'll never win.
i swear i thought you were a wild dog,
snarling and baring your teeth, got me on guard,

Bridge:
she's been gone ever since that night,
all i have left is her old undershirt to hold tight.
you spin me right round, don't even think twice,
tossing your inbox out, girl, you ain't playing nice.

Outro:
all these people, they so fake,
ain't got no cards for them in my deck,

Intro:

rollin' round like the rain, no time to cater.

Chorus 1:

Verse 2:

but they still wanna copy me too, it's like a curse.
don't come at me with nothing, i'm too bold
and the heat between us is just too cold.
i got mo money, that's just how i roll
rocking valentino, always by the ounce, never in control.

Chorus 2:
ice, ice baby, too cold, got scars on my soul,
double d's on my sticks, and your diamonds all dressed up in gold.
waiting for someone to change, to switch sides
but in my heart, i'll always confide.

Verse 3:
gimme that sugar fix, i'm on my groove thang quick,
we move together like two, nothing can break us in two.
always by the ounce, stay on that grind,
tell me why you expected me to miss you, you must be blind,
next to my bed at night, i realize your lies,
but i gotta keep moving, no time to cry.
i put the running into my run,
now your mama's crying, realizing how far i've come.

Chorus 3:
bitch, i'm in the streets, that's where i thrive

bitch, i'm moon, shining bright, never gonna break.
you talk big but you ain't got nothin',
